x4freetext: The 3.2 Mv PELLETRON Accelerator of the
Research Laboratory For Nuclear Reactors at the Tokyo
Thick Lithium Target on a Copper Disk 3.0 Cm
Diameter Ond 0.4 mm Thick. Diameter of Lithium Layer
Is 2.0 Cm. Lithium Target was Bombarded  with 1.5
Nanosec Proton Bunches. Proton Energy was Set to
1.902 MeV, Pulse Repetition Rate 2 Mhz For 10-80 KeV
Measurements, and 1.948 MeV, Pulse Repetition Rate
4 Mhz For 10-150 KeV Measurements. Average Proton
Current is 5.3 or 9.2 Micro-A For 10-80 and 10-150
Scintillation Detector For Neutron Flux Monitoring
Spectrometer was Centered in a 25.4-Cm Outer Diam.
Detector. Energy Resolution of the (HPGE) Detector
Is 1.9 KeV at 1333 KeV Gamma Energy
.Teflon C-F2 Disks with Diameter 90 mm, Chemical Purity
.Corrections were Made For the Count Leakage, Attenu-
Ation of Neutron Monitor Counts Due to the Sample,
Self-Shielding and Multiple Scattering of Neutrons
In Sample, For the Scattering and Absorption of Gamma-
Rays in Sample, For the Dependence of the Gamma-Ray
Detection Efficiency on Gamma Source Position, For
The Effect of Pulse-Height Discrimination ( LESS THAN
0.5 MEV) On the Capture Yield of 197Au, For Dead Time
Full-Energy-Peak Efficiency and Weighting Function of
Final Energy Level of the Gamma
Spin of the Final Level of Gamma Transition
Parity of the Final Level of Gamma Transition
Spin or Parity of Final Level Known with
.Momentum L - Angular Momentum of the Emitted Photons
